# MealMate — Project Overview

A mobile app that helps users optimize grocery shopping for meal prep using real-time store inventory and AI-powered routing.

## Tech Stack

| Layer       | Technology                        |
| ----------- | --------------------------------- |
| Frontend    | React Native (Expo) + TypeScript  |
| Map Engine  | Mapbox SDK (`@rnmapbox/maps`)     |
| Backend     | FastAPI (Python 3.11+)            |
| Database    | PostgreSQL + PostGIS               |
| Cache       | Redis                             |
| AI          | Gemini 1.5 Flash (via LangChain)  |

## External APIs

- **Google Places API** — store location search
- **Mapbox Directions API** — traffic-aware routing
- **Kroger API** — real-time inventory data
- **Serper.dev** — Google Shopping scraper for stores without open APIs
- **Spoonacular API** — recipe data and ingredient substitution

## Project Structure

```
MealMate/
├── frontend/   React Native app
├── backend/    FastAPI server
└── docker-compose.yml
```

## Key User Flow

1. User selects a recipe → AI extracts ingredients
2. User marks what they already have → system builds shopping list
3. System scans stores within 2–5 miles radius (tiered: Walmart > Whole Foods > CVS)
4. If all items found → show Mapbox route
5. If items missing → AI suggests alternative recipes using available ingredients
